<L>__{interior hood dining room. day}
<A>__{one by one, each member of the hood carried in a final item to place on the overstuffed thanksgiving table. then, one by one, they each silently take their seats. they look over the table. no one moves.}
<C>__{ben}
<D>__{well, it's great we can all be together. and this thanksgiving, no hysteria, no yelling, especially with grandpa not here, although we miss him. so let's do it right and actually, wendy, why don't you say grace. you used to love to say grace, remember.}
<A>__{wendy grimaces, as they all bow their heads slightly.}
<C>__{wendy}
<D>__{dear lord, thank you for thanksgiving, and for letting us white people kill all the indians...}
<A>__{everyone looks up.}
<C>__{wendy }
<D>__{... and steal their tribal lands and stuff ourselves like pigs}
<A>__{mutterings and groans: "wendy!" "for christ's sake" etc.}
<C>__{wendy }
